AD_FIELD.NAME: Date printed
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Date the document was printed.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the Date that a document was printed.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Total Paid
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Total amount paid.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Total amount paid.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Process Now
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A request to process the respective document or task.
AD_FIELD.HELP: When this field is set as 'Y' a process is being performed on this record.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Sales Order
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A unique and often automatically generated identifier for a sales order.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Unique identifier and a reference to a Sales Order originating from the document sequence defined for this document type.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Last Calculated on Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Last Calculated On Date for payment monitor
AD_FIELD.HELP: Last Calculated On Date for payment monitor

AD_FIELD.NAME: Payment Method
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: It is the method by which payment is expected to be made or received.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Organizational entity within client
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Currency
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An accepted medium of monetary exchange that may vary across countries.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the currency to be used when processing this document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Charge Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The amount of a cost or expense incurred during business activity.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Charge Amount indicates the amount for an additional charge.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Gross Unit Price
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Price inclusive of taxes
AD_FIELD.HELP: This is the price that is provided when the price is inclusive of taxes.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Generate Receipt from Invoice
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Create and process delivery Receipt from this invoice. The invoice should be correct and completed.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Create and process delivery Receipt from this invoice. The invoice should be correct and completed.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Sales Campaign
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An advertising effort aimed at increasing sales.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Campaign defines a unique marketing program. Projects can be associated with a pre defined Marketing Campaign. You can then report based on a specific Campaign.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Price includes Tax
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Tax is included in the price
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Tax Included checkbox indicates if the prices include tax. This is also known as the gross price.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Project
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Identifier of a project defined within the Project & Service Management module.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Identifier of a project defined within the Project & Service Management module.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Description
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A space to write additional related information.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A description is limited to 255 characters.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Total Net Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The final sum of all line totals made to a specified document or transaction (not including taxes).
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Total amount displays the total of all lines in document currency

AD_FIELD.NAME: Print
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A reference stating whether or not the document has been printed at any time in the past.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Printed checkbox indicates if this document or line will included when printing.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Line Net Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The final amount of a specified line, based only on quantities and prices.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the line net amount based on the quantity and the actual price. Any additional charges or freight are not included.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document Status
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The Document Status indicates the status of a document at this time.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Document Status indicates the status of a document at this time. To change the status of a document, use one of the buttons usually located at the bottom of the document window.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Order Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The time listed on the order.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the Date an item was ordered.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Line Gross Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Gross Amount for a line
AD_FIELD.HELP: This is the total amount against a line ( i.e product price * quantity + taxes )

AD_FIELD.NAME: Price List
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A catalog of selected items with prices defined generally or for a specific partner.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Price Lists are used to determine the pricing, margin and cost of items purchased or sold.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Returned
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Returned
AD_FIELD.HELP: If it is checked means that the debt/payment has been returned by the bank.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document No.
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An often automatically generated identifier for all documents.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The document number is usually automatically generated by the system and determined by the document type of the document. If the document is not saved, the preliminary number is displayed in "<>". If the document type of your document has no automatic document sequence defined, the field will be empty when creating a new document. This is for documents which usually have an external number (like vendor invoice). If you leave the field empty, the system will generate a document number for you. The document sequence used for this fallback number is defined in the "Document Sequence" window with the name "DocumentNo_<TableName>", where TableName is the actual name of the table inside the database (e.g. C_Order).

AD_FIELD.NAME: Tax Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Tax Date
AD_FIELD.HELP: Tax Date

AD_FIELD.NAME: Creation Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The date that this record is completed.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Print Discount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An option to have any discount printed on the invoice.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Discount Printed Checkbox indicates if the discount will be printed on the document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Accounting Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The date this transaction is recorded for in the general ledger.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The date this transaction is recorded on in the general ledger. This date also indicates which accounting period within the fiscal year this transaction will be part of.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Total Outstanding
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Outstanding Amount
AD_FIELD.HELP: Outstanding Amount. Amount pending to be paid

AD_FIELD.NAME: Days Till Next Due
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Days Till Next Due
AD_FIELD.HELP: Number of days left for the next due date

AD_FIELD.NAME: UOM
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A non monetary unit of measure.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The UOM defines a unique non monetary unit of measure

AD_FIELD.NAME: Asset
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An item which is owned and exchangeable for cash.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Any item of economic value owned by the corporation, especially that which could be converted to cash.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Processed
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A confirmation that the associated documents or requests are processed.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Processed checkbox indicates that a document has been processed.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Operative Quantity
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The number of a certain item involved in the transaction, according to the defined Operative UOM.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The number of a certain item involved in the transaction, according to the defined Operative UOM.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Activity
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A distinct activity defined and used in activity based management.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Activities indicate tasks that are performed and used to utilize Activity based Costing

AD_FIELD.NAME: Trx Organization
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The organization which performs or initiates the transaction.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The organization which performs or initiates this transaction (for another organization). The owning Organization may not be the transaction organization in a service bureau environment, with centralized services, and inter-organization transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: 2nd Dimension
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A display of optional elements that are previously defined for this account combination.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The user defined element displays the optional elements that have been defined for this account combination.

AD_FIELD.NAME: User/Contact
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An acquaintance to reach for information related to the business partner.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The User identifies a unique user in the system. This could be an internal user or a business partner contact

AD_FIELD.NAME: Update Payment Monitor
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Invoice Payment Monitor update process
AD_FIELD.HELP: Updates payment monitor info

AD_FIELD.NAME: Transaction Document
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The specific document type which should be used for the document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Specifies document subtype (eg. POS Order, Return Material, etc.) that each document (such as Sales Invoice, Purchase Order, etc.). Various document subtypes usually differ on the consequences they have. You can convert document types (e.g. from Offer to Order). The conversion is then reflected in the current type.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Copy Lines
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Copy lines (products) from an existing Invoice.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Copy lines (products) from an existing Invoice. By selecting any existing past invoice, the process will copy all lines (products) from it to the one currently being edited. This process can be used repetitively to copy lines (products) from several invoices into a new one.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Order Reference
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A reference or document order number as listed in business partner application.
AD_FIELD.HELP: This can be used to input a reference for this specific transaction. For example, a Purchase Order number can be input on a Sales Order for easier reference.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Line No.
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A line stating the position of this request in the document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the unique line for a document. It will also control the display order of the lines within a document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Invoice
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A document listing products, quantities and prices, payment terms, etc.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Invoice ID uniquely identifies an Invoice Document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Process Invoice
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Process Invoice
AD_FIELD.HELP: Process Invoice

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Withholdingamount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Withholding amount

AD_FIELD.NAME: Sales Transaction
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An indication that a transfer of goods and money between business partners is occurring.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Sales Transaction checkbox indicates if this item is a Sales Transaction.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Amount Currently Due
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Due Amount
AD_FIELD.HELP: Total amount due

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A value defining what sequence and process setup are used to handle this document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Document Type determines document sequence and processing rules

AD_FIELD.NAME: Sales Representative
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The person in charge of a document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the sales representative responsible for the transaction that the document specifies . A valid sales representative is a business partner marked as an employee and a sales representative.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Form of Payment
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The method used for payment of this transaction.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Form of Payment indicates the method of payment used for this transaction (eg. cash, wire transfer, etc.)

AD_FIELD.NAME: Withholding
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Withholding

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Product
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An item produced by a process.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Identifies an item which is either purchased or sold in this organization.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Business Partner
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Anyone who takes part in daily business operations by acting as a customer, employee, etc.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Business Partner is anyone with whom you transact. This can include a customer, vendor, employee or any combination of these.

AD_FIELD.NAME: 1st Dimension
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A display of optional elements that are previously defined for this account combination.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The user defined element displays the optional elements that have been defined for this account combination.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Create Lines From
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An addition of statements from pre-existing documents.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A process that allows the user to copy lines (products) from an existing document different from the one being copied into. For example, in case of entering a new Goods Shipment, the user can copy lines (products) from an existing Sales Order or Sales Invoice.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Invoice Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The time listed on the invoice.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Date Invoice indicates the date printed on the invoice.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Charge
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A cost or expense incurred during business activity.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Charge indicates a type of Charge (Handling, Shipping, Restocking)

AD_FIELD.NAME: Calculate Promotions
AD_FIELD.HELP: Calculates and applies the promotions that can valid for the current document modifying final prices if any of them is applicable.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Payment Complete
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A confirmation stating whether the request has been closed through a monetary transaction.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The document is paid for.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Invoiced Quantity
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The total number of a product included in an invoice to a business partner.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Invoiced Quantity indicates the quantity of a product that have been invoiced.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Total Gross Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The final monetary amount (including taxes) charge listed in a document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Grand Total displays the total amount including Tax and Freight in document currency

AD_FIELD.NAME: Posted
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An accounting status button that indicates if the transaction has already been posted to the general ledger or not.
AD_FIELD.HELP: An accounting status button that indicates if the transaction has already been posted to the general ledger or not. When doing the accounting manually this button can be used to post or unpost the transaction from the general ledger by hand.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Partner Address
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The location of the selected business partner.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Partner address indicates the location of a Business Partner

AD_FIELD.NAME: Self-Service
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Self-Service allows users to enter data or update their data. The flag indicates, that this record was entered or created via Self-Service or that the user can change it via the Self-Service functionality.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Self-Service allows users to enter data or update their data. The flag indicates, that this record was entered or created via Self-Service or that the user can change it via the Self-Service functionality.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Cost Center
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Division that adds to the cost of an organization
AD_FIELD.HELP: Division that adds to the cost of an organization. Internal structure for cost allocation.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Gross Unit Price
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Price inclusive of taxes
AD_FIELD.HELP: This is the price that is provided when the price is inclusive of taxes.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Payment Terms
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The setup and timing defined to complete a specified payment.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Payment Terms identify the method and timing of payment for this transaction.
